Description: # zxpy
        
        Shell scripts made simple
        
        > Note: Work in progress. Most of the functionality will be added pretty soon
        
        ## Installation
        
        `pip install zxpy`
        
        ## Example
        
        Make a file `example.zxpy`
        
        ```python
        #! /usr/bin/env zxpy
        ~'echo Hello world!'
        
        file_count = ~'ls -1 | wc -l'
        
        ~"echo 'file count is:'"
        print(file_count)
        ```
        
        Output:
        
        ```bash
        $ ./example.zxpy
        Hello world!
        File count is:
        9
        ```
        
